snapshot.content:
**Team Name:** Biscuits-Krishna

**Course:** SER 516 Software Agility

The biscuit tool is an open-source command-line tool that can be utilized for following the agile software development approach. It has multiple commands that allow features such as creating user stories, planning sprints, planning releases, etc. The tool is based on Java 1.8 and is easy to run across any operating system environment. The tool is intuitive enough and commands are easy to follow.

**Github Link:** [https://github.com/gauthamkun/Biscuits-Krishna (Links to an external site.)](https://github.com/gauthamkun/Biscuits-Krishna)

**Taiga Link:** [https://tree.taiga.io/project/gkrish23-biscuits-krishna/backlog (Links to an external site.)](https://tree.taiga.io/project/gkrish23-biscuits-krishna/backlog)

**Integration Video Link:** \-[https://youtu.be/h7NX3ltOu6g](https://youtu.be/h7NX3ltOu6g)

**Demo link**: -[https://youtu.be/9kCfLHAcoUs](https://youtu.be/9kCfLHAcoUs)

* * *
